{
  "id": "019d33d1-c632-7b13-8dd0-bf9e5414d8ac",
  "content": "# Spoke Dashboard Integration Design (2026-03-28)\n\n## Key Decision: Enhance AgentsView, not a separate SpokesView\nSpokes are agents with extra metadata (container, issue, branch). Enrich existing Agents tab instead of creating a parallel tab. One command center for all agents.\n\n## Backend: 1 new endpoint\n- GET /api/dashboard/spokes - returns Docker container metadata for spoke containers (via bollard). Frontend merges with agent registry data by matching agent_id.\n- Spoke count added to status endpoint.\n\n## Frontend: Enhance existing components\n- AgentCard gets spoke badge + spoke info section (issue, branch, container health)\n- SpokesSummaryBar at top of AgentsView (running count + issue pills)\n- ContainerStatus component (dual health: Docker container + corvia agent heartbeat)\n- Activity feed entries from spokes get spoke badge\n- Agent filter on activity feed for per-spoke view\n- No new tabs, no new pages, no new navigation concepts\n\n## Dual Health Monitoring\n- Docker HEALTHCHECK (pgrep claude) for container-level health\n- corvia agent heartbeat for Claude Code activity\n- Dashboard shows both: container_state + agent_state\n\nDoc: docs/decisions/2026-03-28-spoke-dashboard-design.md",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
